falsely profound and profoundly false about 9/11 , b writes , `` at a pinch we can say that they did it , but we wished for it . . . . we are far beyond ideology and politics now . . . . as if the power bearing these towers suddenly lost all energy , all resilience ; as though that arrogant power suddenly gave way under too intense an effort : the effort always to be the unique world model . '' despite the silliness of these ideas , here and there b does make an interesting point . but the book exists primarily to exhibit b 's cleverness rather than to illuminate terrorism .